#. <section class="sutta" id="sn44.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn44.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 44"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 44"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Abyākatavagga"
msgstr "1. The Undeclared Points"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn44.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Anurādhasutta"
msgstr "2. With Anurādha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "sn44.2:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā anurādho bhagavato avidūre araññakuṭikāyaṃ "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Anurādha was staying not far from the Buddha in a "
"wilderness hut."

msgctxt "sn44.2:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā aññatitthiyā paribbājakā yenāyasmā anurādho "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā anurādhena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then several wanderers who follow other paths went up to Venerable Anurādha "
"and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn44.2:1.4"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnā kho te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā āyasmantaṃ anurādhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one "
"side and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn44.2:1.5"
msgid ""
"“yo so, āvuso anurādha, tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso "
"paramapattipatto, taṃ tathāgato imesu catūsu ṭhānesu paññāpayamāno paññāpeti:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Anurādha, when a Realized One is describing a Realized One—a "
"supreme person, highest of people, who has reached the highest point—they "
"describe them in these four ways:"

msgctxt "sn44.2:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘"
"hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘neva hoti na na hoti "
"tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"After death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and "
"doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist.”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:1.7"
msgid ""
"“Yo so, āvuso, tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso paramapattipatto, taṃ "
"tathāgato aññatra imehi catūhi ṭhānehi paññāpayamāno paññāpeti:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, when a Realized One is describing a Realized One—a supreme "
"person, highest of people, who has reached the highest point—they describe "
"them other than these four ways:"

msgctxt "sn44.2:1.8"
msgid ""
"‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘"
"hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, neva hoti na na hoti "
"tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”ti."
msgstr ""
"After death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and "
"doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist.”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:1.9"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā āyasmantaṃ anurādhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "When he said this, the wanderers said to him:"

#. VAR: cāyaṃ → yo cāyaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn44.2:1.10"
msgid ""
"“so cāyaṃ bhikkhu navo bhavissati acirapabbajito, thero vā pana bālo "
"abyatto”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This mendicant must be junior, recently gone forth, or else a foolish, "
"incompetent senior mendicant.”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā āyasmantaṃ anurādhaṃ navavādena ca "
"bālavādena ca apasādetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then, after rebuking Venerable Anurādha by calling him “junior” and “foolish”"
", the wanderers got up from their seat and left."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.381"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmato anurādhassa acirapakkantesu aññatitthiyesu paribbājakesu "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr "Soon after they had left, Anurādha thought:"

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.2"
msgid "“sace kho maṃ te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā uttariṃ puccheyyuṃ, "
msgstr "“If those wanderers were to inquire further, "

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.3"
msgid ""
"kathaṃ byākaramāno nu khvāhaṃ tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ vuttavādī "
"ceva bhagavato assaṃ, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyaṃ, dhammassa "
"cānudhammaṃ byākareyyaṃ, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"āgaccheyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"how should I answer them so as to repeat what the Buddha has said, and not "
"misrepresent him with an untruth? How should I explain in line with his "
"teaching, so that there would be no legitimate grounds for rebuke and "
"criticism?”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anurādho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā "
"anurādho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Anurādha went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and told him what had happened."

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.5"
msgid "“idhāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato avidūre araññakuṭikāyaṃ viharāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, sambahulā aññatitthiyā paribbājakā yenāhaṃ "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā mayā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.7"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnā kho, bhante, te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā maṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.8"
msgid ""
"‘yo so, āvuso anurādha, tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso "
"paramapattipatto, taṃ tathāgato imesu catūsu ṭhānesu paññāpayamāno paññāpeti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.9"
msgid "“hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.10"
msgid "“neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.11"
msgid "Evaṃ vuttāhaṃ, bhante, te aññatitthiye paribbājake etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.12"
msgid ""
"‘yo so, āvuso, tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso paramapattipatto, taṃ "
"tathāgato aññatra imehi catūhi ṭhānehi paññāpayamāno paññāpeti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.13"
msgid "“hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.14"
msgid "“neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.15"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā maṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.16"
msgid ""
"‘so cāyaṃ bhikkhu navo bhavissati acirapabbajito thero vā pana bālo "
"abyatto’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho maṃ, bhante, te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā navavādena ca bālavādena "
"ca apasādetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.18"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, acirapakkantesu tesu aññatitthiyesu paribbājakesu "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:2.19"
msgid ""
"‘sace kho maṃ te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā uttariṃ puccheyyuṃ, kathaṃ "
"byākaramāno nu khvāhaṃ tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ vuttavādī ceva "
"bhagavato assaṃ, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyaṃ, dhammassa "
"cānudhammaṃ byākareyyaṃ, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"āgaccheyyā’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:3.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn44.2:3.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:4.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:5.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:6.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to "
"be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn44.2:7.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:8.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:9.1"
msgid "“Vedanā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:9.2"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:9.3"
msgid "Saññā … pe …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:9.4"
msgid "saṅkhārā … pe …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:9.5"
msgid "“viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:10.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:11.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:12.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:13.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to "
"be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn44.2:13.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:14.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.383"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Tasmātiha, anurādha, yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā "
"bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, "
"sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“So, Anurādha, you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or "
"present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or "
"near: <em>all</em> form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am "
"not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn44.2:15.2"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā atītānāgatapaccuppannā … pe …"
msgstr "Any kind of feeling …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:15.3"
msgid "yā kāci saññā … pe …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:15.4"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā … pe …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:15.5"
msgid ""
"yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ "
"vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘"
"netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya "
"daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse "
"or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: <em>all</em> consciousness—with "
"right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn44.2:15.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, anurādha, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmimpi nibbindati, vedanāyapi "
"nibbindati, saññāyapi nibbindati, saṅkhāresupi nibbindati, viññāṇasmimpi "
"nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, "
"feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn44.2:15.7"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn44.2:15.8"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:16.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "Do you regard the Realized One as form?”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.4"
msgid "“Vedanaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you regard the Realized One as feeling …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.5"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.6"
msgid "“Saññaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.7"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.8"
msgid "“Saṅkhāre tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.9"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.10"
msgid "“Viññāṇaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness?”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.11"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.12"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.13"
msgid "rūpasmiṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "Do you regard the Realized One as in form?”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.14"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.15"
msgid "“Aññatra rūpā tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Or do you regard the Realized One as distinct from form?”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.16"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.17"
msgid "“Vedanāya … pe …"
msgstr "“Do you regard the Realized One as in feeling …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.18"
msgid "aññatra vedanāya … pe …"
msgstr "or distinct from feeling …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.19"
msgid "saññāya … pe …"
msgstr "as in perception …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.20"
msgid "aññatra saññāya … pe …"
msgstr "or distinct from perception …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.21"
msgid "saṅkhāresu … pe …"
msgstr "as in choices …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.22"
msgid "aññatra saṅkhārehi … pe …"
msgstr "or distinct from choices …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.23"
msgid "viññāṇasmiṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "as in consciousness …"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.24"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.25"
msgid "“Aññatra viññāṇā tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "or as distinct from consciousness?”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:16.26"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

# This passage is unclear, see discussion at https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/a-problematic-reading-in-the-yamaka-sutta/2944
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.384"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "sn44.2:17.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.2"
msgid ""
"rūpaṃ, vedanaṃ, saññaṃ, saṅkhāre, viññāṇaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Do you regard the Realized One as possessing form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness?”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.4"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.5"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ so arūpī avedano asaññī asaṅkhāro aviññāṇo tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Do you regard the Realized One as one who is without form, feeling, "
"perception, choices, and consciousness?”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. VAR: saccato thetato tathāgate anupalabbhiyamāne → saccato vā tathato vā anupabbhanīyasabhāvo (s1, s2) | saccato vā tathato vā anupalabbhiyamāno (s3, mr) | saccato thetato tathāgate anupalabbhyamāne (pts1) | saccato thetato tathāgate anupalabbhamāne (?)
#. VAR: veyyākaraṇaṃ → vyākaraṇāya (bj)
msgctxt "sn44.2:17.7"
msgid ""
"“Ettha ca te, anurādha, diṭṭheva dhamme saccato thetato tathāgate "
"anupalabbhiyamāne kallaṃ nu te taṃ veyyākaraṇaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“In that case, Anurādha, since you don’t acknowledge the Realized One as a "
"genuine fact in the present life, is it appropriate to declare:"

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.8"
msgid ""
"yo so, āvuso, tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso paramapattipatto, taṃ "
"tathāgato aññatra imehi catūhi ṭhānehi paññāpayamāno paññāpeti:"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, when a Realized One is describing a Realized One—a supreme "
"person, highest of people, who has reached the highest point—they describe "
"them other than these four ways:"

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.9"
msgid "‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"After death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and "
"doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist’?”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.10"
msgid "‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.11"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.12"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, anurādha."
msgstr "“Good, good, Anurādha!"

msgctxt "sn44.2:17.13"
msgid ""
"Pubbe cāhaṃ, anurādha, etarahi ca dukkhañceva paññāpemi dukkhassa ca "
"nirodhan”ti."
msgstr ""
"In the past, as today, what I describe is suffering and the cessation of "
"suffering.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn44.2:17.14"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
